Movie Trailer Website version 1.0 13/07/2015

GENERAL USAGE NOTES
-------------------

Run Website
-----------
In order to run the website execute the following command:
python main.py

Then a file fresh_tomatoes.html is generated.


Add Movies to Website
---------------------
The collections of movies that is going to be displayed on the website is passed to
the function open_movies_page() of the file fresh_tomatoes.py as a list of movie classes.

Each movie class requires a title, story line, poster image url and trailer url.

For example:

Movie class of Toy Story:
toy_story = movie.Movie("Toy Story", "A story of a boy and his toys that come to life",
                        "http://www.filmandtvnow.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Toy-Story-Characters1.jpg",
                        "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KYz2wyBy3kc")

movies = [toy_story]
fresh_tomatoes.open_movies_page(movies)

This would display exactly one movie which is Toy Story and a trailer of it is played when it is clicked on.


Requirements
------------
    - webbrowser module
    - fresh_tomatoes.py file from Udacity's course "Programming Foundation with Python"